This paper deals with privacy-preserving mechanisms in location-based services, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves designing algorithms to quantify privacy leakage, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper deals with data management and privacy in location-based services, which is related to database systems (cs.DB) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
